This paper analyzes the emotional content of words and its impact on communication, which falls under the field of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also uses statistical analysis to examine the frequency and informativeness of words, which could be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The study of social links and communication could also fall under social and information networks (cs.SI) and cybernetics (cs.CY). Finally, the paper's focus on language and communication could be relevant to software engineering (cs.SE) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
